  "text": "CA1 hippocampal pyramidal neurons receive tens of thousands of synaptic inputs each. How information, transmitted by these inputs, is processed in CA1 dendrites to produce meaningful output is not well understood. Dendrites contain an abundance of ion channels which can impact synaptic integration and which are subject to activity-dependent modulation during synaptic plasticity [CITATION_1] , the leading model of information storage in neurons.",
